Here is a summary of the input text:

The story follows Mira, a girl who can communicate with trees, and her relationship with the ancient Grandfather Cedar. After sensing an urgent feeling of "danger" and "fire" from the tree, Mira tries to warn the local rangers, who dismiss her concerns due to the wet season. Mira realizes the threat is internal—a sickness spreading through the roots rather than an external wildfire. She leads the village children to treat the infected trees with a sap mixture. When a small fire does eventually start due to a careless hiker, the healthy trees successfully resist it, allowing the rangers to contain the blaze. Mira's success is celebrated when the forest responds with a feeling of gratitude, and the villagers claim to hear the redwoods singing.